# 1. Install

make dev-install

# 2. Drop your GROQ_API_KEY into .env

cp .env.example .env

# 3. Place data

# - MedQA JSONL files in data/raw/medqa/

# - 18 textbook .txt/.md in data/raw/textbooks/

# 4. Build indices

make index

# 5. Smoke-test

make test-unit
make api # then visit http://localhost:8000/docs

# 6. Run an architecture

make run-naive # or run-self / run-hybrid / run-multihop
make run-all # all four + comparison report under results/reports/
Known follow-ups (not blockers):

Drop in real MedQA JSONL files — the loader handles both common schemas.
The RagasEvaluator calls Groq's judge model directly; if RAGAS ≥ 0.2 needs explicit LangChain LLM wiring, swap in a LangchainLLMWrapper around GroqClient.complete.
LIME/SHAP wrappers run sequential Groq calls per perturbation — bound num_samples to 30–50 in settings.yaml until you size the budget.
